extends layout

block content
  // /.container-fluid
  .container.text-center
    // HEADER
    .page-header
      h1 Matters of Privacy
      p
        | In this test we will be looking at how expression recognition could play a part in online communication. This test looks at simple text-based communication as an example.
    // CONTENT
    .row
      .col-sm-6.text-left
        h2 Why
        p
          | Video calling is massive today. Facebook, Skype and most major operating systems include some form of video calling functionality. But not everyone wants their face to be shown, whether it's for security reasons or otherwise.
        p
          | Could we use some sort of avatar to show our own real-time facial expressions instead of showing our faces?
      .col-sm-6.text-left
        h2 How
        p
          | When you press begin test, the facial expression mimicking avatar will appear for 15 seconds.
        p Make some faces!
    .row
      a.btn.btn-default.btn-lg(href='/', role='button') Back
      a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(href='/scenario_3_active', role='button') Begin Scenario